the heat of a campaign to get their respective leaders elected. Practitioners and political scientists collaborate to present real-world insights that demystify over a dozen occupations, including campaign chairs, fundraisers, advertisers, platform designers, communication personnel, election administrators, political staff, journalists, and pollsters. Inside the Campaign provides an inside look at, and unparalleled understanding of, the nuts and bolts of running a federal campaign in Canada.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aCampaign managementzCanada. 0aPolitical campaignszCanada. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Political Process / Campaigns & Elections.2bisacsh1 aBooth, Donald, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrin, Colette, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChenery, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCollombat, Thomas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCormier, Michel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCrandall, Erin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDeCillia, Brooks, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDelacourt, Susan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEsselment, Anna Lennox, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGiasson, Thierry, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGiasson, Thierry, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGrenier, Éric, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLalancette, Mireille, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLawlor, Andrea, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/rela